hopobject.body: I work for a publishers half day diet review 24 hour While the 13.4 percent HIV prevalence in the general population in the country is one of the highest on the African continent, Namibia has made great progress showing a decline in new infections. This is from an estimated 10 000 in 2008 to 8 000 in 2011. Namibia has also succeeded in reducing mother to child transmission of HIV, with five percent of infants born with HIV last year.
